						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall, central shrine, Nāchchiyammaṉ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 5: 976 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 70 sheep by the association of temple-devotees <hi rend="italic">(panmāhēśvaras)</hi> after the scrutiny of temple accounts, to the goddess of bhaṭṭāraki of Tiruchcheṅguḷam adjacent to Būdalūr in Ēri-nāḍu. The shepherds Aiṉōvaṟiyagaṉ and Aiṉōkambaṉ received the sheep and agreed to measure out daily three <hi rend="italic">piḍi</hi> of ghee (obviously for burning a perpetual lamp).</p>						

						</summary>
